  "title": "PRODUCTION ASSISTANT / LINE PRODUCER",
  "description": "<p><p>- Keep shoots moving and timelines alive (even when plans change every 5 minutes)<br />- Handle logistics, schedules, and all the “who’s where now?” questions<br />- Support producers + directors so they can focus on the creative<br />- Coordinate crew, talent, transport, food, and locations (yes, food matters)<br />- Be on set to solve problems before they become full-blown drama<br />- Stay calm, stay sharp, and adapt fast — production waits for no one<br /><br /><strong>IMPORTANT: </strong><br />- Cool with travelling OFTEN and staying away from home when work calls<br /><br /><strong>Bonus points if you:</strong><br /><strong>- </strong>Have on-set experience<br />- Can think fast and stay calm<br />- Understand budgets, timelines, and real-world production limits<br />- Love problem-solving more than complaining</p></p>",
